68Address FunctionTemplateInfo::callback(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate) const {
69 Address result = maybe_redirected_callback(isolate);
70 if (!USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL) return result;
71 if (result == kNullAddress) return kNullAddress;
72 return ExternalReference::UnwrapRedirection(result);
73}
74
75void FunctionTemplateInfo::init_callback(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate,
76 Address initial_value) {
77 init_maybe_redirected_callback(isolate, initial_value);
78 if (USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL) {
79 init_callback_redirection(isolate);
80 }
81}
82
83void FunctionTemplateInfo::set_callback(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate,
84 Address value) {
85 set_maybe_redirected_callback(isolate, value);
86 if (USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL) {
87 init_callback_redirection(isolate);
88 }
89}
90
91void FunctionTemplateInfo::init_callback_redirection(
92 i::IsolateForSandbox isolate) {
93 CHECK(USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL);
94 Address value = maybe_redirected_callback(isolate);
95 if (value == kNullAddress) return;
96 value =
97 ExternalReference::Redirect(value, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
98 set_maybe_redirected_callback(isolate, value);
99}
100
101void FunctionTemplateInfo::remove_callback_redirection(
102 i::IsolateForSandbox isolate) {
103 CHECK(USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL);
104 Address value = callback(isolate);
105 set_maybe_redirected_callback(isolate, value);
106}

108EXTERNAL_POINTER_ACCESSORS_MAYBE_READ_ONLY_HOST(
109 FunctionTemplateInfo, maybe_redirected_callback, Address,
110 kMaybeRedirectedCallbackOffset, kFunctionTemplateInfoCallbackTag)

112template <class IsolateT>
113bool FunctionTemplateInfo::has_callback(IsolateT* isolate) const {
114 return !IsTheHole(callback_data(kAcquireLoad), isolate);
115}

117// static
118Tagged<FunctionTemplateRareData>
119FunctionTemplateInfo::EnsureFunctionTemplateRareData(
120 Isolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info) {
121 Tagged<HeapObject> extra =
122 function_template_info->rare_data(isolate, kAcquireLoad);
123 if (IsUndefined(extra, isolate)) {
124 return AllocateFunctionTemplateRareData(isolate, function_template_info);
125 } else {
126 return FunctionTemplateRareData::cast(extra);
127 }
128}
129
130#define RARE_ACCESSORS(Name, CamelName, Type, Default) \
131 DEF_GETTER(FunctionTemplateInfo, Get##CamelName, Tagged<Type>) { \
132 Tagged<HeapObject> extra = rare_data(cage_base, kAcquireLoad); \
133 Tagged<Undefined> undefined = \
134 GetReadOnlyRoots(cage_base).undefined_value(); \
135 return extra == undefined ? Default \
136 : FunctionTemplateRareData::cast(extra)->Name(); \
137 } \
138 inline void FunctionTemplateInfo::Set##CamelName( \
139 Isolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info, \
140 Handle<Type> Name) { \
141 Tagged<FunctionTemplateRareData> rare_data = \
142 EnsureFunctionTemplateRareData(isolate, function_template_info); \
143 rare_data->set_##Name(*Name); \
144 }
145

147RARE_ACCESSORS(prototype_provider_template, PrototypeProviderTemplate,
148 HeapObject, undefined)
149RARE_ACCESSORS(parent_template, ParentTemplate, HeapObject, undefined)
150RARE_ACCESSORS(named_property_handler, NamedPropertyHandler, HeapObject,
151 undefined)
152RARE_ACCESSORS(indexed_property_handler, IndexedPropertyHandler, HeapObject,
153 undefined)
154RARE_ACCESSORS(instance_template, InstanceTemplate, HeapObject, undefined)

157RARE_ACCESSORS(access_check_info, AccessCheckInfo, HeapObject, undefined)
158RARE_ACCESSORS(c_function_overloads, CFunctionOverloads, FixedArray,
159 GetReadOnlyRoots(cage_base).empty_fixed_array())
160#undef RARE_ACCESSORS

162InstanceType FunctionTemplateInfo::GetInstanceType() const {
163 int type = instance_type();
164 DCHECK(base::IsInRange(type, Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType,
165 Internals::kLastJSApiObjectType));
166 return static_cast<InstanceType>(type);
167}
168
169void FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceType(int api_instance_type) {
170 // Translate |api_instance_type| value from range
171 // [Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType,
172 // Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType] to range
173 // [Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType, Internals::kLastJSApiObjectType].
174 DCHECK_LE(Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType, api_instance_type);
175 DCHECK_LE(api_instance_type, Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType);
176 // kNoJSApiObjectType must correspond to JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE.
177 static_assert(kNoJSApiObjectType == 0);
178 static_assert(JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE == Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType);
179 set_instance_type(static_cast<InstanceType>(
180 api_instance_type + Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType));
181}
182
183void FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRange(
184 int api_instance_type_start, int api_instance_type_end) {
185 // Translate |api_instance_type_start| and |api_instance_type_end| values
186 // from range [Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType,
187 // Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType] to range
188 // [Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType, Internals::kLastJSApiObjectType].
189 DCHECK_LE(Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType, api_instance_type_start);
190 DCHECK_LE(api_instance_type_start, api_instance_type_end);
191 DCHECK_LE(api_instance_type_end, Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType);
192 // kNoJSApiObjectType must correspond to JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE.
193 static_assert(kNoJSApiObjectType == 0);
194 static_assert(JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE == Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType);
195 set_allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start(static_cast<InstanceType>(
196 api_instance_type_start + Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType));
197 set_allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end(static_cast<InstanceType>(
198 api_instance_type_end + Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType));
199}
200
201// Ensure that instance type fields in FunctionTemplateInfo are big enough
202// to fit the whole JSApiObject type range.
203static_assert(
204 FunctionTemplateInfo::AllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRangeStartBits::is_valid(
205 LAST_JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE));
206static_assert(
207 FunctionTemplateInfo::AllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRangeEndBits::is_valid(
208 LAST_JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE));

213bool TemplateInfo::is_cached() const { return serial_number() > kUncached; }

216 return IsSharedFunctionInfo(shared_function_info());
217}

219inline bool FunctionTemplateInfo::BreakAtEntry(Isolate* isolate) {
220 Tagged<Object> maybe_shared = shared_function_info();
221 if (IsSharedFunctionInfo(maybe_shared)) {
222 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = SharedFunctionInfo::cast(maybe_shared);
223 return shared->BreakAtEntry(isolate);
224 }
225 return false;
226}

228Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> FunctionTemplateInfo::GetParent(Isolate* isolate) {
229 Tagged<Object> parent = GetParentTemplate();
230 return IsUndefined(parent, isolate) ? Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo>{}
231 : FunctionTemplateInfo::cast(parent);
232}
233
234Tagged<ObjectTemplateInfo> ObjectTemplateInfo::GetParent(Isolate* isolate) {
235 Tagged<Object> maybe_ctor = constructor();
236 if (IsUndefined(maybe_ctor, isolate)) return ObjectTemplateInfo();
237 Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> constructor =
238 FunctionTemplateInfo::cast(maybe_ctor);
239 while (true) {
240 constructor = constructor->GetParent(isolate);
241 if (constructor.is_null()) return ObjectTemplateInfo();
242 Tagged<Object> maybe_obj = constructor->GetInstanceTemplate();
243 if (!IsUndefined(maybe_obj, isolate)) {
244 return ObjectTemplateInfo::cast(maybe_obj);
245 }
246 }
247 return Tagged<ObjectTemplateInfo>();
248}

279bool TemplateInfo::TryGetIsolate(Isolate** isolate) const {
280 if (GetIsolateFromHeapObject(*this, isolate)) return true;
281 Isolate* isolate_value = Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
282 if (isolate_value != nullptr) {
283 *isolate = isolate_value;
284 return true;
285 }
286 return false;
287}

289Isolate* TemplateInfo::GetIsolateChecked() const {
290 Isolate* isolate;
291 CHECK(TryGetIsolate(&isolate));
292 return isolate;

295// static
296template <typename ReturnType>
297MaybeHandle<ReturnType> TemplateInfo::ProbeInstantiationsCache(
298 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
299 int serial_number, CachingMode caching_mode) {
300 DCHECK_NE(serial_number, TemplateInfo::kDoNotCache);
301 if (serial_number == TemplateInfo::kUncached) {
302 return {};
303 }
304
305 if (serial_number < TemplateInfo::kFastTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize) {
306 Tagged<FixedArray> fast_cache =
307 native_context->fast_template_instantiations_cache();
308 Handle<Object> object{fast_cache->get(serial_number), isolate};
309 if (IsTheHole(*object, isolate)) {
310 return {};
311 }
312 return Handle<ReturnType>::cast(object);
313 }
314 if (caching_mode == CachingMode::kUnlimited ||
315 (serial_number < TemplateInfo::kSlowTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize)) {
316 Tagged<SimpleNumberDictionary> slow_cache =
317 native_context->slow_template_instantiations_cache();
318 InternalIndex entry = slow_cache->FindEntry(isolate, serial_number);
319 if (entry.is_found()) {
320 return handle(ReturnType::cast(slow_cache->ValueAt(entry)), isolate);
321 }
322 }
323 return {};
324}

326// static
327template <typename InstantiationType, typename TemplateInfoType>
328void TemplateInfo::CacheTemplateInstantiation(
329 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
330 DirectHandle<TemplateInfoType> data, CachingMode caching_mode,
331 Handle<InstantiationType> object) {
332 DCHECK_NE(TemplateInfo::kDoNotCache, data->serial_number());
333
334 int serial_number = data->serial_number();
335 if (serial_number == TemplateInfo::kUncached) {
336 serial_number = isolate->heap()->GetNextTemplateSerialNumber();
337 }
338
339 if (serial_number < TemplateInfo::kFastTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize) {
340 Handle<FixedArray> fast_cache =
341 handle(native_context->fast_template_instantiations_cache(), isolate);
342 Handle<FixedArray> new_cache =
343 FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate, fast_cache, serial_number, object);
344 if (*new_cache != *fast_cache) {
345 native_context->set_fast_template_instantiations_cache(*new_cache);
346 }
347 data->set_serial_number(serial_number);
348 } else if (caching_mode == CachingMode::kUnlimited ||
349 (serial_number <
350 TemplateInfo::kSlowTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize)) {
351 Handle<SimpleNumberDictionary> cache =
352 handle(native_context->slow_template_instantiations_cache(), isolate);
353 auto new_cache =
354 SimpleNumberDictionary::Set(isolate, cache, serial_number, object);
355 if (*new_cache != *cache) {
356 native_context->set_slow_template_instantiations_cache(*new_cache);
357 }
358 data->set_serial_number(serial_number);
359 } else {
360 // we've overflowed the cache limit, no more caching
361 data->set_serial_number(TemplateInfo::kDoNotCache);
362 }
363}
364
365// static
366template <typename TemplateInfoType>
367void TemplateInfo::UncacheTemplateInstantiation(
368 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
369 DirectHandle<TemplateInfoType> data, CachingMode caching_mode) {
370 int serial_number = data->serial_number();
371 if (serial_number < 0) return;
372
373 if (serial_number < TemplateInfo::kFastTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize) {
374 Tagged<FixedArray> fast_cache =
375 native_context->fast_template_instantiations_cache();
376 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(fast_cache->get(serial_number), isolate));
377 fast_cache->set(serial_number, ReadOnlyRoots{isolate}.the_hole_value(),
378 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
379 data->set_serial_number(TemplateInfo::kUncached);
380 } else if (caching_mode == CachingMode::kUnlimited ||
381 (serial_number <
382 TemplateInfo::kSlowTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize)) {
383 Handle<SimpleNumberDictionary> cache =
384 handle(native_context->slow_template_instantiations_cache(), isolate);
385 InternalIndex entry = cache->FindEntry(isolate, serial_number);
386 DCHECK(entry.is_found());
387 cache = SimpleNumberDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, cache, entry);
388 native_context->set_slow_template_instantiations_cache(*cache);
389 data->set_serial_number(TemplateInfo::kUncached);
390 }
391}
